getRunContent

@Deprecated
public java.util.List<java.lang.Object> getRunContent()
Deprecated. 

Gets the value of the runContent property.

This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the runContent property.

For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

    getRunContent().add(newItem);

Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<FldChar> JAXBElement<R.EndnoteRef> JAXBElement<CTFtnEdnRef> JAXBElement<R.SoftHyphen> JAXBElement<R.NoBreakHyphen> JAXBElement<CTFtnEdnRef> JAXBElement<R.Separator> JAXBElement<R.PgNum> JAXBElement<CTRuby> JAXBElement<R.YearShort> JAXBElement<R.Tab> JAXBElement<R.CommentReference> JAXBElement<Text> JAXBElement<R.MonthLong> JAXBElement<R.Ptab> JAXBElement<R.Sym> JAXBElement<R.FootnoteRef> JAXBElement<Text> JAXBElement<R.LastRenderedPageBreak> JAXBElement<CTObject> JAXBElement<R.MonthShort> JAXBElement<Pict> Br JAXBElement<R.AnnotationRef> JAXBElement<R.DayShort> JAXBElement<Text> JAXBElement<R.Cr> JAXBElement<R.YearLong> JAXBElement<Drawing> JAXBElement<R.ContinuationSeparator> JAXBElement<R.DayLong> DelText
